      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUKA DONCIC NZ (2) has been racing well of late. Missed by head when runner-up from the second line two back at this circuit and distance then drew wide and finished fourth at his latest appearance over further. At peak fitness now and is likely to get the favours from this nice draw. Big chance. MONOPOLLIE (10) has been quite consistent of late and turned in a good run here last time out when third from a  similar barrier. With even luck he could find his way to the winners' stall. TAYLORS FOUR (1) draws much better than last start and was a Redcliffe winner prior, also from a wider barrier. MINI MINE YET NZ (3) is another drawn well and is worth thought off a last-start win by 3 metres at this circuit and distance.",
